subject: World Cup (Skiing)
Skiing
lead_paragraph: Maria Holaus of Austria broke through for her first World Cup victory and Julia Mancuso of the United States was left winless this season when she finished second again.Holaus took advantage of an early start position in Cortina d’Ampezzo, Italy, to win a sunny super-G, covering the melting Olympia delle Tofane course in 1 minute 24.63 seconds.Mancuso finished 0.23 of a second behind, and the overall World Cup leader Nicole Hosp of Austria was third, 0.28 back.
